Uses of Package
de.mslab.core

  • Packages that use de.mslab.core 
    Package Description
    de.mslab.bicliquesearch
    Provides classes which implement the biclique finding process.
    de.mslab.bicliquesearch.helpers  
    de.mslab.ciphers
    Provides classes which represent implementations of popular block ciphers.
    de.mslab.ciphers.helpers
    Provides helper classes which count the number of active bits or bytes in non-linear operations in the matching phase for the individual block ciphers.
    de.mslab.core
    Provides classes which represent byte arrays, differences, differentials and bicliques.
    de.mslab.diffbuilder
    Provides helper classes which are required for biclique creation, such as to construct differences for bit-wise or byte-wise operating ciphers, or to compare differentials for their independency.
    de.mslab.matching
    Provides classes which are required to compute the matching part of biclique attacks, and to compute the complexity of biclique attacks.
    de.mslab.rendering
    Provides classes which are responsible to render bicliques, matching phases, and the contained differentials, with state and key differences at their rounds.
    de.mslab.utils
    Provides utility classes.
